	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-09-18T20:05:18">Polar Capital Technology Trust plc is a United Kingdom-based diversified, closed ended alternative investment fund. The Fund's investment objective is to maximize long-term capital growth through investing in a diversified portfolio of technology companies across the world. The Fund invests in technology companies, which use technology or which develop and supply technological solutions as a core part of their business models. The Fund invests in the areas, including information, media, communications, environmental, healthcare, financial and renewable energy, computing and associated industries. The Fund invests up to 85% of its portfolio in North America; up to 40% of its portfolio in Europe; up to 55% of its portfolio in Japan and Asia, and up to 10% of its portfolio in the rest of the world. Polar Capital LLP is the Fund's investment manager, as well as its alternative investment manager.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-12-31T06:48:32">BRIEF: For the six months ended 31 October 2015, Polar Capital Technology Trust plc revenues decreased 90% to L11.6M. Net income decreased 94% to L6.7M. Revenues reflect Gains on investments held at fair value decrease of 94% to L7.2M, Other currency (losses)/gains decrease of 37% to L407K. Net income also reflects Other administrative expenses increase of 6% to L402K (expense).</Text>
